6. Aboard the Apollo 16 lunar landing mission, astronauts were selected by NASA. Thomas K. Mattingly II (command module pilot), John W. Young (commander) and Charles M. Duke Jr. (lunar module pilot). Apollo 16 was the tenth manned mission for the United Sates Apollo program. pic.twitter.com/ojpRR42W4a
1. Apollo 16 was the second last mission of the Apollo program and became the fifth to successfully land astronauts on the moon and return them safely to earth. # AS511pic.twitter.com/B3c8H4lukb

The U.S. Apollo program was designed to safely land human astronauts on the moon and return them back to Earth. Apollo 16 was the 5th of 6 missions to land men on the lunar surface and return them back to Earth safely. PIC: Apollo 16 mission crest. pic.twitter.com/jwaastzt8h
